Author: Samantha York (NEWS CENTER Maine)

PORTLAND, Maine â€” Composer and pianist Ben Cosgrove has always had an obsession with the natural world around him.

That love for geography helped inspire the music on his new album, "Topograph," which is set to be released Jan. 30. This is Cosgrove's sixth studio album.

"I usually describe myself as a geography nerd trapped in the body of a piano player," Cosgrove said. "This is sort of a way I figured out to like dig into these landscapes and topographies and geologies I'm really interested in."

